lead_paragraph: A $213.2 million bond offering by California State Public Works was initially priced yesterday to yield a maximum 5.30 percent for a bond due in 2009 through underwriters led by Lehman Brothers. The remaining serial refunding revenue bonds were priced to yield from 2.85 percent in 1994 to 4.05 percent in 1998, 4.80 percent in 2003 and 5.25 percent in 2008.
